State of the Repository Report

2022-12-09 08:47:54

Rick Gilmore

Purpose

This document summarizes information about Databrarys holdings, partners, and citations. It draws upon datasets specific to these categories that are generated elsewhere.

Community

The Databrary community consists of Institutions and their Authorized Investigators. Authorized Investigators may, in turn, grant access to Affiliates whose access they supervise.

Growth

new_stats <- databraryapi::get_db_stats()
new_stats$date <- lubridate::as_datetime(new_stats$date)

new_stats <- new_stats %>%
  dplyr::select(date, institutions, investigators, affiliates) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(date = lubridate::as_datetime(date))
if (purrr::is_empty(new_stats)) {
  stop("Unable to retrieve new statistics from Databrary.")
}
if (params$from_gs) {
  db <- googlesheets::gs_title('Databrary-analytics')
  
  old_stats <- db %>%
    googlesheets::gs_read(ws = 'institutions-investigators')
} else {
  old_stats <- readr::read_csv("csv/institutions-investigators.csv", show_col_types = FALSE)
}
old_stats <- old_stats %>%
  dplyr::mutate(., date = lubridate::as_datetime(date))
 # initialize updated_stats
updated_stats <- old_stats
if (as.logical(params$update_stats)) {
  next_entry <- dim(updated_stats)[1] + 1
  updated_stats[next_entry, ] = NA
  
  # fill with new data
  # updated_stats$date[next_entry] <- new_stats$date
  # updated_stats$institutions[next_entry] <- new_stats$investigators
  # updated_stats$investigators[next_entry] <- new_stats$investigators
  # updated_stats$affiliates[next_entry] <- new_stats$affiliates
  updated_stats[next_entry, ] <- new_stats
}

# Calculate change
n_rows <- dim(updated_stats)[1]

delta_investigators <- updated_stats$investigators[n_rows] - updated_stats$investigators[n_rows - 1]

delta_institutions <- updated_stats$institutions[n_rows] - updated_stats$institutions[n_rows - 1]
 
# filter NAs
updated_stats <- updated_stats %>%
  dplyr::filter(., !is.na(affiliates),
         !is.na(investigators),
         !is.na(affiliates),
         !is.na(date))
# Create a tidy form for plotting both institutions and investigators and affiliates
gathered_stats <- updated_stats %>%
  tidyr::gather(., key = "type", value = "count", -date) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(date = lubridate::as_date(date)) %>%
  dplyr::select(date, count, type) %>%
  dplyr::filter(type %in% c('institutions', 'investigators')) %>%
  dplyr::filter(!is.na(count))

# Plot
users_plot <- gathered_stats %>%
  ggplot(., aes(
    x = date,
    y = count,
    color = type,
    group = type
  )) +
  scale_x_date(date_labels = "%Y", date_breaks = '1 year') +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line(size = ln_size) +
  scale_colour_manual(values = c(color_orange, color_teal)) +
  ggtitle(paste("Authorizations as of ", Sys.Date())) +
  ylab("Authorizations") +
  databrary_theme +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0, plyr::round_any(max(
    gathered_stats$count
  ), 100, ceiling), 100), expand = c(0, 0)) +
  coord_cartesian(ylim = c(0, plyr::round_any(max(
    gathered_stats$count
  ), 100, ceiling)))

cowplot::ggdraw(users_plot) +
  cowplot::draw_label(paste0(
    "Investigators: ", updated_stats$investigators[n_rows],
    " (+ ", delta_investigators, ")"), colour = color_teal, .65, .8) +
  cowplot::draw_label(paste0(
    "Institutions: ", updated_stats$institutions[n_rows],
    " (+ ", delta_institutions, ")"), colour = color_orange, .75, .5)

if (as.logical(params$update_gs)) {
  db <- db %>%
    gs_add_row(ws = 'institutions-investigators', 
               input = new_stats)
  message("'update_gs' parameter is 'TRUE', so Google Sheet data will be updated.")
} else {
  message("'update_gs' parameter is 'FALSE', so Google Sheet data unmodified.")
}
if (as.logical(params$update_csv)) {
  if (!purrr::is_empty(updated_stats)) {
  readr::write_csv(updated_stats, "csv/institutions-investigators.csv")
  message("Updated 'csv/institutions-investigators.csv'.")    
  } else {
    message("No new institutions or investigator data to write.")
  }
}

Volumes

A dataset or a collection of research materials is stored as a volume on Databrary.

Growth

new_stats <- databraryapi::get_db_stats()
new_stats$date <- lubridate::as_datetime(new_stats$date)
if (params$from_gs) {
  db <- googlesheets::gs_title('Databrary-analytics')
  old_vols <- db %>%
    googlesheets::gs_read(ws = 'volumes-shared-unshared')
} else {
  old_vols <- readr::read_csv("csv/volumes-shared-unshared.csv")
}

if (purrr::is_empty(old_vols)) {
  stop("No old data loaded.")
}
# Filter NAs
updated_vols <- old_vols %>%
  dplyr::filter(., !is.na(shared_volumes),
                !is.na(unshared_volumes),
                !is.na(date))  

if (as.logical(params$update_stats)) {
  next_entry <- dim(updated_vols)[1] + 1
  updated_vols[next_entry,] = NA
  
  updated_vols$date[next_entry] <- new_stats$date
  if (is.null(new_stats$datasets_shared)) {
    new_stats$datasets_shared = 0
  }
  updated_vols$shared_volumes[next_entry] <- new_stats$datasets_shared
  updated_vols$unshared_volumes[next_entry] <- 
    new_stats$datasets_total - new_stats$datasets_shared
}


# Calculate change
n_rows <- dim(updated_vols)[1]

delta_shared <- updated_vols$shared_volumes[n_rows] - updated_vols$shared_volumes[n_rows - 1]

delta_unshared <- updated_vols$unshared_volumes[n_rows] - updated_vols$unshared_volumes[n_rows - 1]

updated_vols <- updated_vols %>%
  dplyr::filter(., !is.na(shared_volumes),
                !is.na(unshared_volumes),
                !is.na(date))

gathered_vols <- updated_vols %>%
  tidyr::gather(., key = "type", value = "count", -date)
# Plot
vols_plot <- gathered_vols %>%
  ggplot(., aes(
    x = date,
    y = count,
    color = type,
    group = type
  )) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line(size = ln_size) +
  scale_colour_manual(values = c(color_orange, color_teal)) +
  ggtitle(paste("Volumes as of ", Sys.Date())) +
  ylab("Volumes") +
  databrary_theme +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0, plyr::round_any(max(
    gathered_vols$count
  ),
  100, ceiling), 100),
  expand = c(0, 0)) +
  coord_cartesian(ylim = c(0, plyr::round_any(max(
    gathered_vols$count
  ),
  100, ceiling)))

cowplot::ggdraw(vols_plot) +
  cowplot::draw_label(
    paste0(
      "Unshared: ",
      updated_vols$unshared_volumes[n_rows],
      " (+",
      delta_unshared,
      ")"
    ),
    colour = color_teal,
    .6,
    .85
  ) +
  cowplot::draw_label(
    paste0(
      "Shared: ",
      updated_vols$shared_volumes[n_rows],
      " (+",
      delta_shared,
      ")"
    ),
    colour = color_orange,
    .75,
    .50
  )

if (as.logical(params$update_gs)) {
  db <- db %>%
    gs_add_row(ws = 'volumes-shared-unshared', input = updated_vols)
} else {
  message("'update_gs' parameter is 'false', so Google Sheet data unmodified.")
}
if (as.logical(params$update_csv)) {
  if (!is_empty(updated_vols)) {
    readr::write_csv(updated_vols, "csv/volumes-shared-unshared.csv")
    message("Updated 'csv/volumes-shared-unshared.csv'.")    
  } else {
    message("No new volumes data to write.")
  }
}

How shared

get_volume_name <- function(vol_id) {
  vol_metadata <- databraryapi::list_volume_metadata(vol_id)
  if (!is.null(vol_metadata)) {
    as.character(vol_metadata$name)
  } else {
    NULL
  }
}

vols_sess_data <- readr::read_csv("../shared-volumes-sessions/csv/shared_volumes_sessions.csv", show_col_types = FALSE)

vols_dat <- vols_sess_data %>%
  # change variable names, create full_volume vs. overview_only
  dplyr::group_by(owner_ids.name, owner_ids.id) %>%
  dplyr::rename(investigator = owner_ids.name, party_id = owner_ids.id) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(shared_type = ifelse(sharing_level == "full", "full_volume", "overview_only")) %>%
  dplyr::select(investigator,
                party_id,
                vol_id,
                created_date,
                shared_type,
                n_sessions) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(url = paste0("https://nyu.databrary.org/party/", party_id)) %>%
  dplyr::group_by(investigator, url, shared_type) %>%
  # summarise by total shared volumes by type with session stats
  dplyr::summarise(
    n_vols = n(),
    tot_sess = sum(n_sessions),
    min_n_sess = min(n_sessions),
    max_n_sess = max(n_sessions)
  ) %>%
  dplyr::arrange(shared_type, desc(tot_sess))

unique_vols <- vols_sess_data %>%
  dplyr::rename(., investigator = owner_ids.name, party_id = owner_ids.id) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(.,
                shared_type = ifelse(sharing_level == "full", 
                                     "full_volume", "overview_only")) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(., vol_url = paste0("https://nyu.databrary.org/volume/", vol_id)) %>%
  dplyr::group_by(., vol_id, vol_name, vol_url, created_date, shared_type, n_sessions) %>%
  dplyr::summarise(., n_owners = n())

Types of data

Databrary specializes in storing and sharing video and audio recordings, but the system supports the storage of other file types, see https://nyu.databrary.org/asset/formats. The following summarizes the composition of currently shared data:

#quietly_read_csv <- safely(readr::read_csv)

if (dir.exists('../volume-assets/csv')) {
  csv_fns <- list.files('../volume-assets/csv', '\\.csv', full.names = TRUE)
  assets_df <- purrr::map_df(csv_fns, readr::read_csv, show_col_types = FALSE)
} else {
  stop(paste0('CSV directory not found: ', '../volume-assets/csv'))
}

Participant demographics

Databrary encourages users doing research with human participants to report demographic data in a structured format so that others may more easily find and reuse data relevant to their questions.

load_demog_csvs <- function(dir = "../participant-demographics/csv") {
  if (!is.character(dir)) {
    stop("'dir' must be a string")
  }
  if (!dir.exists(dir)) {
    stop("'dir' does not exist.")
  }
  
  fl <- list.files(dir, "[0-9]{4}-sess-materials\\.csv$", full.names = TRUE)
  if (is.null(fl)) {
    stop(paste0("No csv files in ", dir, "."))
  }
  purrr::map_dfr(fl, read.csv, colClasses = "character")
}

demo_df <- load_demog_csvs()

Citations

We mine the Google Scholar database to estimate the number of citations to Databrary or Datavyu.

if (params$from_gs) {
  db <- googlesheets::gs_title('Databrary-analytics')  

  old_citations <- db %>%
    googlesheets::gs_read(ws = 'citations-monthly')
} else {
  old_citations <- readr::read_csv("csv/citations-monthly.csv", show_col_types = FALSE)
}

old_citations <- old_citations %>%
  dplyr::mutate(date = lubridate::as_date(date))
# Get citation counts from Google Scholar
get_citation_stats <- function(project = 'databrary') {
  if (project %in% c('databrary', 'Databrary')) {
    url <-
      'https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&as_sdt=1%2C39&as_vis=1&q=%22databrary%22+%22Databrary%22&btnG='
  } else if (project %in% c('datavyu', 'Datavyu')) {
    url <-
      'https://scholar.google.com/scholar?hl=en&as_sdt=1%2C39&as_vis=1&q=%22Datavyu%22+%22datavyu%22&btnG='
  }
  
  r <- httr::GET(url = url)
  if (httr::status_code(r) == 200) {
    content <- httr::content(r, 'text')
  } else {
    message(paste0('Download Failed, HTTP status ', httr::status_code(r)))
  }
  
  n_results <-
    stringr::str_match(content, pattern = "About ([0-9]+)")[2]
  if (is.null(n_results)) {
    message(paste0('Unable to parse results from search.'))
    return(NULL)
  } else {
    return(as.numeric(n_results))
  }
}

databrary_cites <- get_citation_stats('databrary')
datavyu_cites <- get_citation_stats('datavyu')
# Merge old with new
citations <- old_citations
if (as.logical(params$update_stats)) {
  next_value <- dim(old_citations)[1] + 1
  citations[next_value, ] <- NA
  
  citations$date[next_value] <- lubridate::as_date(Sys.Date())
  citations$databrary_citations[next_value] <- databrary_cites
  citations$datavyu_citations[next_value] <- datavyu_cites
}

# Calculate change
n_rows <- dim(citations)[1]
delta_db_cites <-
  citations$databrary_citations[n_rows] - citations$databrary_citations[n_rows - 1]
delta_dv_cites <-
  citations$datavyu_citations[n_rows] - citations$datavyu_citations[n_rows - 1]

# Filter NAs
citations <- citations %>%
  dplyr::filter(.,!is.na(date),
                !is.na(databrary_citations),
                !is.na(datavyu_citations))
gathered_citations <- citations %>%
  tidyr::gather(., key = "type", value = "count", -date)

# Plot
citations_plot <-
  gathered_citations %>%
  ggplot(., aes(
    x = date,
    y = count,
    color = type,
    group = type
  )) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line(size = ln_size) +
  scale_colour_manual(values = c(color_orange, color_teal)) +
  ggtitle(paste("Citations as of ", Sys.Date())) +
  ylab("Citations") +
  databrary_theme +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0, plyr::round_any(
    max(gathered_citations$count),
    100, ceiling
  ), 100),
  expand = c(0, 0)) +
  coord_cartesian(ylim = c(0, plyr::round_any(
    max(gathered_citations$count), 100, ceiling
  )))

cowplot::ggdraw(citations_plot) +
